---
import CTABand from '@/components/sections/CTABand.astro'
import { SITE_URL } from '@/consts'
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro'
import { jsonLd } from '@/utils/json-ld'

const organizationSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Organization',
  name: 'Adaptive Alchemy',
  url: SITE_URL,
  logo: `${SITE_URL}/assets/adaptive-alchemy-logo.png`,
  description:
    'Product and technology strategy leadership firm providing fractional CTO services, technical due diligence, and AI transformation advisory to growth-stage companies and their investors.',
  knowsAbout: [
    'AI Strategy',
    'Fractional CTO',
    'Product Strategy',
    'Technical Due Diligence',
    'AI Transformation',
    'Technology Assessment'
  ],
  serviceType: [
    'Fractional CTO Services',
    'Fractional CPTO Services',
    'Product & Technology Strategy Review',
    'Investor Readiness',
    'AI Transformation Advisory',
    'CTO Coaching'
  ]
}
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="Adaptive Alchemy is a collective of senior product and technology strategists who embed in your organization to solve product strategy, architecture, velocity, and AI transformation challenges."
>
  <script
    is:inline
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={jsonLd(organizationSchema)}
  />
  <section class="px-6 py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl text-text-primary md:text-5xl">
        Transform how you build.
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
        <p>
          Adaptive Alchemy is a product and technology strategy leadership firm.
          We work as fractional CPTOs: one leader who owns both product
          direction and engineering execution, rather than splitting those
          responsibilities and hoping they align. We also run technical due
          diligence and AI transformation engagements for growth-stage companies
          and their investors.
        </p>

        <p>
          Most companies at this stage end up with separate product and
          technology leadership that requires constant coordination. We skip
          that problem. One leader owns both. Product priorities and engineering
          decisions stay connected without a layer of alignment work in between.
        </p>

        <p>
          We start with strategy, but we stay through delivery. When more hands
          are needed to execute, we bring in engineers we have worked with
          before and stay responsible for the quality of what ships.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-12 font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary">
          Why &ldquo;Alchemy&rdquo;?
        </h2>

        <p>
          Alchemy was about transformation, but only through deep understanding
          of the material. That is how we approach product and technology
          organizations. Before we change anything, we understand what is
          actually broken and why. The diagnosis is most of the work. The
          transformation follows from it.
        </p>

        <p>
          The companies getting real value from AI are treating agents the way
          they treat engineers, with clear responsibilities, production
          standards, and accountability for outcomes. We help organizations
          build that way, because we operate that way ourselves.
        </p>

        <p>
          The experience behind this work spans decades, across financial
          services, enterprise software, data infrastructure, and retail. It
          covers every stage from early startups through Fortune 50 enterprises,
          and it runs both sides of the hard problems: technical leadership and
          commercial transformation. Most of what actually blocks companies
          lives at the seam between those two.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-12 font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary">
          What we believe
        </h2>

        <ul class="space-y-4">
          <li class="border-l-2 border-gold/30 pl-4">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">
              Velocity is a clarity problem.
            </strong>
            Slow teams are almost never lazy or under-resourced. They are unclear
            on what they are building and why. Fix the clarity, the velocity follows.
          </li>
          <li class="border-l-2 border-gold/30 pl-4">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">Structure beats talent.</strong>
            Talented engineers in the wrong system produce mediocre results. The same
            engineers with clear priorities, real autonomy, and no coordination waste
            can move remarkably fast.
          </li>
          <li class="border-l-2 border-gold/30 pl-4">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">
              Agent-first is an operating model, not a toolset.
            </strong>
            Adding AI tools to existing workflows captures a fraction of the value.
            Redesigning workflows around what agents can do reliably. That is where
            the compounding starts.
          </li>
          <li class="border-l-2 border-gold/30 pl-4">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">
              Please-to-thank-you time is the metric that matters.
            </strong>
            From stakeholder request to delivered business value. That number reflects
            everything: clarity, architecture, team structure, process waste. When
            it shrinks, the whole system is working better.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand />
</PageLayout>
